        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        You Gotta Understand It.
        Ill start this review off by stating Im 37 years old so this for me is ( perfect ) I seen alot of online reviews of people criticizing this game emulator.Initially I brought this as a gift for my niece to play when boredom strikes simply because of the volume of games.And of course people harp on ( it has repeat games ) who cares when you can really enjoy alot of classic childhood games fromContra,Galaga,Pacman,Double Dragon, Ninja Turtles,Mario, Sonic, Street Fighter,King Of Fighter, Pokemon,Golden Axe, Altered Beast , Excite Bike , Need For Speed ,Mortal Kombat , X-Men ,Lion King , Battle Toads , Dig Dug , GI Joe listen to me seriously the list goes on and on.Next is the ability to ( save the game ) its great as well to pick up where you left off so its unlimited lives and re-tries plus some games allow you to max out tokens.Controls yep the are not the best but the buttons are able to be mapped ( so you can change them to your liking ) the analog is not great but its not a dealbreaker either the Directional pad is ( alright ) to get the job done. So fighter games will be a lil bit more difficult. But scrolling games are no problemI now own two because I kept this game for my self and bought my niece another one. Hopefully she enjoys it what great for me is to play games I missed out on or could beat in my youth so yes playing ( Punch Out ) and finally winning was great.If you want a legit game system buy a console I completely understand I own a ( PS4 ) . But for travel and the ability to connect to the HDTV and just have access to alot of 80,90s games its worth the price.If you price any PlayStation games or retro consoles and then games sold separately youll understand why this emulator is kinda cool.4 stars
